---
import { providerLine } from "../config";
---

<section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-16 sm:px-8 sm:py-20">
  <div class="reveal mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
    <p class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold leading-snug sm:text-3xl">
      Works with <span class="text-reveal">Claude</span> today.
    </p>
    <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-muted sm:text-lg">
      {providerLine} Houdini's core is provider-agnostic, so every AI you pay for
      slots into the same gauges — and we never show a number we can't honestly read.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
